ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
Higher scores indicate greater levels of empathy during the session
Higher scores indicate greater levels of collaboration during the session

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
What do you believe was your ratio of reflections to questions?
What do you believe was your level of MI proficiency?
How well do you think you stayed focused on session-relevant topics?
How thoroughly were able to assign this week's homework and review the previous homework assignments?
For what percentage of the session do you believe you were the one speaking?
How would you rate the quality of your empathy with this family?
How would you rate the quality of your collaboration with this family?
What percentage of your statements to the client do you believe were consistent with a Motivational Interviewing (MI) approach?
What percentage of your statements to the client do you believe were inconsistent with a Motivational Interviewing (MI) approach?
What percentage of the questions you asked were open-ended (versus close ended)?
What percentage of your reflections you said were complex (versus simple)?
